President Trump has declared a state of emergency in North Carolina due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Florence. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts in order to assist the local population and provide emergency measures to save lives and protect property and public health. FEMA is authorized to mobilize and provide equipment and resources as necessary. The federal funding for emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent. Albert Lewis has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.